<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2355] unsychronized logWriters map is mutated from several threads in HLog splitting</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2355</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In splitLog, the logWriters map is an unsynchronized collection, and the spawned threads mutate it. In practice I&apos;ve now seen several times a situation where one of the puts into this map is lost, and a thread ends up renaming a file it&apos;s in the process of writing to, causing those edits to be lost when the log is split.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
